reviewText: My sons love Bubble Guppies, and we have all of the dvd's Nickelodeon has released so far. This disc has 6 episodes rather than the usual 4. The episodes included have already played on tv, but they are newer ones. I'm happy with this purchase.

This collection includes  "Puppy Love", "Ducks in a Row", "Boy Meets Squirrel", "Lonely Rhino", "The Elephant Trunk-A-Dunk" and "The Arctic Life", six animal-themed episodes taken from the show's first three seasons.  All are of high quality featuring good, entertaining (and lightly educational) adventures that most pre-schoolers and kindergartners should enjoy, plus they probably won't drive parents too far up the wall.  The songs are catchy too, even though their Kidz Bop flavor seems like overkill for the age group.

The DVD itself is hit or miss, from the cropped video presentation (full screen!) to the watered-down Dolby Digital 2.0 mix.  Why "Bubble Guppies" isn't presented in the original widescreen is beyond me, but Nickelodeon is pretty inconsistent in this department.  No bonus features either.  But whether your kids enjoy this show or they're completely new to it, discs like "Animals Everywhere" are a pretty safe bet.

My 2 year old loves Bubble Guppies, as do my 5 and 7 year old.  I think what attracts her to it is the catchy songs they sing, which I admit I find myself singing along.  This DVD has six episodes on it featuring the whole Bubble Guppies gang and their animal friends from a rhino, to elephants to a squirrel and more!  Super cute episodes.  The show is wholesome and teaches great lessons for young kids.  While the episodes are ones that have previously aired on television, it was great to have them on one DVD to watch anytime, anywhere.

Our 18 month old daughter loves Bubble Guppies! She watches it everyday before nap time. This DVD has great episodes with excellent songs. She especially loves the elephant episode with molly singing the ellie ellie ellaphant song. As parents we only have the TV on for her, first thing in the morning (she watches Barney), and before nap time (she watches Bubble Guppies). She's always loved Bubble Guppies and amazon has great prices on Bubble Guppie dvds. Each dvd has 5, 30-40 minute episodes, and in my opinion each episode is the perfect length for one sitting for a toddler. We have 4 Bubble Guppies dvds, and all have great episodes, songs, and the dialogue is educational and entertaining for toddlers. Our daughter loves this show, and so do we as parents.
